# Unified Client Onboarding & Edge Camera Provisioning System

As TuringSight transitions to a mass-deployable Deep Tech platform, manual provisioning of individual camera configuration files (`.env`, `manifest.yaml`), AWS IoT Core mTLS X.509 certificates, policies, and Docker environments becomes a significant bottleneck.

We need a reliable, seamless, and automated system to onboard new clients, register cameras, generate mTLS certificates, provision policies, and output a packaged, deployable edge bundle (`deploy_<camera_id>.zip`).

---

## 📐 System Architecture & Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Admin as Deployment Engineer / Admin API
    participant DBReg as DynamoDB: Camera-Registry
    participant DBPerm as DynamoDB: User-Cameras
    participant IoT as AWS IoT Core (ap-south-1)
    participant FS as Local Filesystem / Packer
    
    Note over Admin, DBPerm: Phase 1: Database Registration
    Admin->>DBReg: Register camera metadata & RTSP URL (cam_id)
    Admin->>DBPerm: Map camera_id to User Cognito ID (user_id)

    Note over Admin, IoT: Phase 2: mTLS Credentials Provisioning
    Admin->>IoT: Call create_keys_and_certificate(setAsActive=True)
    IoT-->>Admin: Return PEM certificate & Private Key contents
    Admin->>IoT: Attach TuringSightEdgePolicy to the new certificate ARN

    Note over Admin, FS: Phase 3: Config Generation & Packaging
    Admin->>FS: Write certificate.pem and private.key files
    Admin->>FS: Copy AmazonRootCA1.pem
    Admin->>FS: Generate config/cam_id.env (with dynamically resolved IoT endpoint)
    Admin->>FS: Generate config/cam_id_manifest.yaml (default rules/anchors)
    Admin->>FS: Generate customized docker-compose.yml for this camera ID
    Admin->>FS: Compress all files to onboard_bundles/deploy_cam_id.zip

    Note over Admin, FS: Phase 4: Edge Delivery
    Admin-->>Admin: Provide deploy_cam_id.zip to Client hardware
```

